comment: ..."On the very same night that JD allegedly assaulted AH, she invited James Franco over to the home she shared with JD"... I know if I had just been through such a terrifying ordeal at the hands of my partner or spouse, the last thing I'd have done would be to have another guy come over to visit me. I'd be far too petrified of my partner giving me another beating. Also, women who go through domestic abuse often go to extreme lengths to hide the fact that they're being victimised. The fear, shame & guilt often felt by the person concerned is usually too powerful to move beyond on their own & often,  as a result of this, women will live with their abuser for years before deciding to take action. Women like Amber Turd with her BS & lies, make it all the more difficult for genuine cases to come forward. It's cases like these that creates doubt & leaves women who are already living in a constant state of terror, all the more anxious about coming forward,  too afraid they wont be believed, protected & kept safe.

comment:
To be honest I don't think Johnny would be a nightmare to live with. I don't know for sure but to be honest I wont base my opinion on anything this compulsive liar has to say.  It is easy to say that but as she constantly goaded him I think the sanest person would get riled.  That doesn't mean they are a nightmare.  Sorry but someone getting annoyed and abusing furnishings is something we all could do if things are going bad.  He was dealing with so much apart from her at the time he abused inanimate objects.  He had received some bad news, his mum also was deteriorating.    I have thrown things at a wall before.   I have broken an ornament or two.  I am sure many have.  I have never thrown something at a person.  I also believe the tales of drug abuse and drinking have been exaggerated by her alot.  From what I understand he went through many dry spells.  An example of people just assuming is the photo with the icecream.  The guy had just done a 17 hour day working and he just looked knackered to me.  The way he fell asleep sitting up crosslegged with his hand in pocket is something I have done many times through exhaustion.   The funniest was when I had just finished a double shift, got home and went to the loo. I woke up several hours later still sitting on the loo.  Lol exhaustion does that haha.  People just assume he had been drinking based on her exaggerations and tall tales.   It is funny some of the photos she has produced, I just think he looks normal. Listening to some of the conversations she had she must have been so draining.  I can imagine him trying to escape and her following him around the house.  Enough to drive the sanest person insane :)

 I think if he was with a  calm loving person he would be a calm loving person.

comment:
I'm starting to believe the saddest of truths....other than such vile accusations is that Amber ACTUALLY BELIEVES WHAT SHE  IS SAYING.  I believe that her illnesses are not allowing her to see the truth. She sees what she wants to see and she truly does believe what she has done, what she says have happened to her and what she says Johnny did to her. She truly believes that she was confused yesterday when she kept changing her story about Cochella. 

I believe she does believe she is not sure which officer she talked to that night. 

I have been in a relationship with someone very, very much like what she is presenting. Luckily, in my case the first time he hit me .  After a year of manipulation, I left. I joke a little (coping mechanism) that he slapped sense into me. This guy had done to me EXACTLY what he claimed a number of other women had done to him. Once each gal figured him out, he bailed and found another victem. At that point it was me.  Or, if he felt his plan falling apart, he found another gal to live off of and left before the old one could dump him. I had several therapists state that he was very, very good at what he did. 
One night he came home from an outing with his friends and pulled a gun on me. That ordeal lasted for over six hours. Finally, it defused and I could go to bed. In the morning, I called friends for help and they ALL said: "funny. He said he was afraid to go home. He said he was terrified that you would pull a gun on him. But, you would tell us all that it was him that had the gun.". Even my friends who had known me four and five times longer than they knew him......believed him. I was quiet, shy and didn't even know how to use a gun. Yet...they all believed him. 
I believe that IF some husband or someone hasn't killed him by now. Or he's not in prison, he is STILL pulling this trick on women. But, one of the scariest parts is that he TOTALLY AND COMPLETELY BELIEVES HIS SIDE. Even with undeniable evidence in front of him, he still fully believed his stories. ALL of them. 
I think amber is the same. I think she does believe that EB heard her, amber incorrectly. I think she will always have a seriously believable....to her....version of what happened. She does not  think she is lying. Which makes her mad when she is questioned. (Although, I wonder if she hasn't taken some kind of tranquilizer so keep her emotions down while she is questioned.) Amber will be told she is/did lie through her teeth. She will be told her stories are weak and don't match up. She will be told the metadata is wrong, the pictures are manipulated, conclusive evidence shows the total opposite of what she says and that she can't prove her case. But, because SHE, in her mind has never, ever lied she won't understand why she is not believed on her word alone. And, in the end....sadly as much as she deserves to be prosecuted for several offences that she has admitted to over the last two days as well as those others have proven she committed, she will NEVER believe she was wrong. And she will never understand why others think she was wrong. It will ALL be a conspiracy against her, in her mind. Prison will never teach her anything. I'm not saying she should not be removed from society. But, if she is, I strongly feel that she will always think she was wronged by Johnny, his friends, family, her friends that testified in his favor, his security team, fans and anyone else she can think of. Its such a shame. And I am no expert other than by experience. But, that is exactly how I think she is and how she will respond in the end. Very sad on all accounts and for all involved. 
I DO hope it gives Johnny some reasonable sort of his life back though.

comment:
To clarify these were not secret recordings, both of them knew they were being recorded. JD and AH would record their arguments to help AH recall what was spoken in these arguments bc she would have a tendency to forget and make up stuff. So to avoid who said what they would begin by recording themselves and come back to them in order to make changes to improve their marriage. They didn't come out before bc in their divorce agreement they would not speak or share stuff about each other. Considering AH first broke that agreement (she didn't clearly use his name in the Washington Post Oped, but clearly referring to JD) probably someone from JD's team leaked the recordings to help get the truth out and give him a fighting chance. 

Also, JD is the strongest man to face this  treacherous demon every day and not retaliate. He was NOT a baby. If an individual is being physically attacked and emotionally controlled with verbal abuse they need to remove themselves. That's exactly what he did he removed himself and left the room so he didn't get that far with her. He wouldn't allow it, and instead chose to self medicate. He would choose to redirect pain on himself before allowing to hurt the one he loved. And, yes he loved her. It took awhile for him to see that the person he loved wasn't really real, it was just a character AH played. He actually says something like this in one of his recordings that she was just a figment of his imagination and she was never there. 

Imagine this he's being adviced to get a prenuptial with AH, decides to finally brings it up, causing her to become enraged, she then throw vodka bottles at him with one actually hitting him, crushing his finger, severing the tip of his figure and shattering his bone, and had to go home to the woman who was his wife that did this to him. Crazy to think about.

He had lied to save her reputation during that whole time. He had multiple procedures and had multiple infections, and AH continued to manipulate the situation and blackmail him. He is not a baby, he was deceived and manipulated. He loved the wrong person, but did his best to care for her. Even when they were separated he was willing to let her stay at the penthouse for as long as she needed, and even allowed her friends (I think it was 6ppl) living there rent free. This man is beyond generous! Go research other YouTubers covering this and check out their older videos on it. You will be amazed what this man went through and still going through. 

AH even hired a private eye to get dirt on JD and the private investor (PI) found through cross examining 100 ppl and I think as far back as 20 years discovered nothing bad but thay he was a nice guy. Not sure about all the details, but you can Google this and check it out yourself. It's hilarious when the outcome was AH who had issues with ppl, more individuals coming out to have issues with her character instead of JD. He found JD was pretty clean and loved. There's just so much I'm really disappointed to not see more coverage of this.
